Method Detail

getData

java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.util.List<java.util.Map<java.lang.String,java.lang.String>>> getData(java.util.Set<java.lang.String> feedIDs,
                                                                                                         java.util.concurrent.TimeUnit timeUnit,
                                                                                                         long startTime,
                                                                                                         long endTime)
Returns a map of data for each feed. This allows the data to be queried in batch and improves performance.

Parameters:
feedIDs - to retrieve data for
timeUnit - the time unit of startTime and endTime parameters.
startTime - the start time of the return data set.
endTime - the end time of the return data set.
Returns:
map of data for the specified feeds. Each entry in the map has data with a timestamp that is >= startTime and < endTime.
